The paper introduces a novel variational RNN model for online prediction and recognition, which is likely to fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The model also involves probabilistic structures and temporal patterns, which could place it under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category. Additionally, the paper tests the model on two datasets involving image and speech recognition, which could place it under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) categories, respectively.
